sentences: Raisa Andriana, better known by her mononym Raisa (born in Jakarta on 6 June 1990), is an Indonesian singer and songwriter.
Prior to her solo career, she was one of the lead vocalist of Kevin Aprilio's band, Andante, which later renamed as Vierra (now Vierratale).
In 2014, she was charted at 45th place on Billboard Uncharted, marking her first time to enter the Billboard chart.
Later in 2017, she reached 29th place on Billboard Social 50, a chart which ranks the most active musical artists on the world's leading social networking services.
Raisa Andriana was born on 6 June 1990 in Jakarta, Indonesia to Allan Rachman and Ria Mariaty.
